# Naming Standards — [ORG_SLUG]

Canonical naming conventions for projects, branches, environments, infrastructure.

## Project / repository naming

- Backend APIs: `api-<domain>` — e.g., `api-billing`, `api-users`
- Frontend apps: `app-<domain>` — e.g., `app-dashboard`, `app-mobile`
- Libraries: `lib-<domain>` — e.g., `lib-shared-types`
- Tools/scripts: `tool-<purpose>` — e.g., `tool-migration-runner`
- <TODO: any custom prefixes for your org>

## Git branch naming

- `feat/<short-description>` — new feature
- `fix/<short-description>` — bug fix
- `chore/<short-description>` — maintenance, dependency bumps
- `docs/<short-description>` — documentation only
- `hotfix/<short-description>` — urgent production fix
- Protected branches: `main`, `test` (or `staging`, depending on org)

## Environment naming

- `dev` — local developer environment
- `test` — automated integration / CI
- `staging` — pre-production for manual QA
- `prod` — production
- <TODO: any custom envs>

## Infrastructure naming

- Hosts: `<role>-<env>-<n>` — e.g., `app-prod-01`, `db-staging-01`
- Containers: same as host where it runs, plus `-<service>`
